Janchi guksu (잔치국수) translated into “banquet or feast noodles,” is a simple warm noodle dish made with thin wheat/rice noodles (소면, somyeon, aka somen) that are usually served in a clear anchovy or beef broth. Because noodles symbolize long and happy lives in Korean culture, this noodle dish is traditionally served alongside other special occasion foods at large feasts such as weddings. The name of the dish comes from that tradition.

The most important part of this humble noodle dish is the broth. Sung Gyung Rice Janchi guksu uses non-fried rice noodle with good texture, the broth is made with Anchovy, dried Laver and other Korean ingredients. It will definitely warm up your tummy with this traditional tasty Rice Noodle.

Janchi guksu (잔치국수) 翻译成“宴会或盛宴面条”，是一种简单的温热面条，由细小麦/米粉（소면，somyeon，又名素面）制成，通常与清澈的凤尾鱼或牛肉汤一起食用。因为面条在韩国文化中象征着长寿和幸福，所以在婚礼等大型宴会上，这种面条传统上与其他特殊场合的食物一起供应。这道菜的名字来自那个传统。

这道不起眼的面条最重要的部分是汤。 Sung Gyung Rice Janchi Guksu 使用质地很好的非油炸米粉，汤是用凤尾鱼、昆布和其他韩国食材制成的。用这种传统美味的米粉肯定会让你的肚子暖和起来。
